args: Thank you, Brother. That's very kind.
Once today's rite of presentation is done,\nyou'll be the Auspex for real—and that's\nwhen things get REALLY busy.
From the moment I was born as one\nwith holy mana, I have been waiting for\nthis day.
Now I can finally be of use to everyone,\nand will do so to the best of my ability.
Well, there's a whole crowd packed into\nthe city square to catch a glimpse of you.
You've got this, Zethia. Go on.
(As the Auspex, I seek to protect this world\nthrough the power of prayer.)
...I won't forget the simple wish\nI held in those days.
I had a place in the world. I had people\nI loved who also loved me in turn.\nI had a world I wanted to protect.
I had a reason to exist. Permission to be.\nBut what have I now? Nothing.
(I have no right to exist in this world,\nforeign to it as I am.)
(At least, not the Zethia you all cherish.)
(The reason you all treat me with such\nkindness is that you see her in me.)
(But none in this world have any cause\nto hold dear an interloper like me.)
(I must do all I can to be of use; to make a\ndifference, however small, so that I might\nearn a true place here.)
It is the Auspex's calling, even if I am\nunable to undertake it with the same pure\nand simple heart I held back then.
I cannot be that person, but please do not\nhate me for it, {player_name}.
*huff* *pant* N-not yet. It is not enough!
(No matter how many times I try,\nthe Other's power within me stifles\nthe flow of the Auspex's mana.)
Elly told me about your training.\nIt's admirable, but are you sure you\naren't pushing yourself too hard?
You look as though a stiff breeze might\ntopple you. If you keep this up, you'll run\nout of mana again and...
I tell you, I've no other choice.
What's driving you here? Why are you\nso adamant to see this thing through?
Because I am not your Zethia!
Apologies. I must go and cool my head.
We can't leave things like this.\nI'll go talk to her.
She's crossed countless worlds and\nexperienced grief almost beyond measure.\nI know she has plenty on her mind.
I'll never know what it's like to be her,\nbut I know we'll come to an understanding\nif we just try.
There you are. Can we talk?
This is about earlier, I assume?
Yes. What did you mean? What does\n＂not being your Zethia＂ have to do with\nyou pushing yourself so hard?
...I am pushing myself so I might\nearn permission to exist here.
For if I bring no benefit to all of you,\nwhat purpose do I even serve?
I am a stranger to this world.\nThat is all, and nothing else.
So you want to perform this rite\nto raise our opinion of you?
And you think that will serve as permission\nfor you to continue existing here?
Yes. For an outsider such as myself,\nit is the only way to carve out a place\nand forge a life with worth and meaning.
Throughout the countless worlds I traveled,\nit has always been thus.
But that's not how belonging works—\nOR how we measure a person's worth.
You've lost allies, been betrayed,\nand probably faced a litany of other\nhorrors I don't even know about.
I know it's hard to trust people,\nbut I want you to know this:
We all consider you our dear friend.
And can you be certain you treasure me\nfor me, and not because I am, in a sense,\nthe Zethia you love above all others?
I can. You are you and no one else—\nand that's all I see when I look at you.
You're right, you know?\nYou're NOT our Zethia.
You're Zena. Zethia's someone else.\nWe're all smart enough to get that.
And knowing this, you would still name me\na friend? You've always seen me that way?
I seem to have misunderstood you all.\nI was off on my own, spinning in circles.
Well, lemme make it super clear:\nWe love the SNOT out of you!
Yet I cannot forgive myself, let alone love\nmyself. You would say such even still?
Without hesitation. And if you can't love\nyourself, we'll just have to love you even\nmore to make up the difference.
What one lacks, another can make up for.\nThat's what it means to be with someone.
Now come on—it's late and getting cold.\nWe should get back to the castle.
(I won't be able to change overnight.\nI cannot love myself, and struggle to\ntrust others.)
(But I WANT to change; I WANT to be\ndifferent for all of them. So I...)
There is something I have been\nkeeping from you all.
And once you hear it, you may not wish\nto name me a friend so freely.
But if I am to be worthy of the trust you\nplaced in me and change myself...
I must tell you my secret.
